FZ ClipFlow

A simple, fast and lightweight downloader designed to make downloading videos, audio and thumbnails easy.

#------ IMPORTANT (FIRST WINDOWS EXECUTION) ------#

When launching FZ ClipFlow for the first time, Windows may display a security warning such as:

"This app is unrecognized and might put your PC at risk."

or

"Windows protected your PC."

This happens because:

→ FZ ClipFlow is not digitally signed
→ It is an independent application distributed outside the Microsoft Store
→ It uses internet-based tools such as yt-dlp

This warning is common for independent software and does not necessarily indicate that the application is malicious.

#------ HOW TO RUN ANYWAY ------#

If Windows SmartScreen appears:

Click "More info"
Click "Run anyway"

The application will start normally.

This procedure is usually required only the first time you run the program.

#------ QUICK FIX ------#

If Windows continues to block the file:

Locate FZ ClipFlow.exe
Right-click the file
Select "Properties"
Check "Unblock" if the option is available
Click "Apply"
Click "OK"
Run the application again

#------ IF WINDOWS BLOCKS OR REMOVES THE FILE ------#

If the executable is blocked or quarantined:

Open Windows Security
Go to "Virus & threat protection"
Open "Protection history"
Locate FZ ClipFlow
Select "Allow on device"

If the issue persists:

Open "Virus & threat protection"
Click "Manage settings"
Scroll to "Exclusions"
Click "Add or remove exclusions"
Click "Add an exclusion"
Choose "File"
Select FZ ClipFlow.exe

Then try running the application again.

